					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Well, I fixed my monitor, replacing all dried up capacitors. Then made the chroma decoder setup procedure using a test signal generator and oscilloscope. The main problem was in the LC contour matching of the delay line. So here's what I've got:<br /><a href="http://savepic.ru/5797661.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="http://savepic.ru/5797661m.jpg" alt="Image" /></a><br />Despite the small jalousie effect in some colors (need to more accurately adjust the LC contour of delay line and the LC contour of color subcarrier) is still colors are the almost same. So the xx6538 Dendy's PPU color coding is correct.</div>

