				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Well, it's pretty logical. There's also a purely digital circuit and a set of frequencies is clearly limited. It does not matter that the frequencies are not multiples of the scanline frequency, the color burst is taken from the same frequency source.<br /><br />I've been thinking. With regards to the PAL. The system uses a delay line. It is designed for exactly 64mks (15625Hz for PAL systems). Thus, if the frequency of the scanlines is slightly changed, the delayed scanline will not be exact to the desired phase, causing color artifacts.</div>

